Customer Behavior Analysis using SQL (SSMS)
📌 Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing a customer dataset using SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS).
The goal is to extract meaningful insights related to customer demographics, purchasing behavior, revenue, and marketing performance.

📂 Dataset Information

The dataset (customer table) contains information such as:

CustomerID
Gender
Customer_Segment
Annual_Income
Quantity & Unit Price
Revenue & Profit Margin
Customer Satisfaction
Purchase Frequency
Purchase Quarter
Marketing Channel
Loyalty Score
Days to Next Purchase
Season



🎯 Key Objectives
Analyze gender distribution and percentages
Identify top customers based on revenue
Understand customer segments and income patterns
Evaluate purchasing behavior
Analyze sales trends (quarter-wise & season-wise)
Measure customer satisfaction and loyalty
Track marketing channel performance






SELECT * FROM customer;

--how many male and female customer we have 
SELECT 
Gender,Count(Gender) As male_per
From customer 
Group by Gender 
Having Gender in ('Male','Female');


-- what is the percentage of male 
SELECT 
(SELECT COUNT(Gender) FROM customer where Gender = 'Male')*100/
COUNT(Gender) as Male_per From customer;


-- what is the percentage of female
SELECT 
(SELECT COUNT(Gender) FROM customer where Gender = 'Female')*100/
COUNT(Gender) as Female_per From customer;


-- how many type of segment in data
SELECT DISTINCT Customer_Segment FROM customer;

-- count different customer segment 
SELECT DISTINCT Customer_Segment, 
COUNT(Customer_Segment) as count_segment FROM customer
Group by Customer_Segment;


-- total segment and income categories by gender
SELECT
Customer_Segment,
COUNT(Customer_Segment) AS MALE_SEGMENT
FROM 
customer WHERE Gender IN ('Male')
Group by Customer_Segment

UNION

SELECT
Customer_Segment,
COUNT(Customer_Segment) AS FEMALE_SEGMENT
FROM 
customer WHERE Gender IN ('Female')
Group by Customer_Segment



--
SELECT 
CustomerID,
Quantity,
Unit_Price,
(Quantity*Unit_Price) as Price
FROM customer;

-- which payment method most use order by all category
SELECT 
Payment_Method,
COUNT(Payment_Method) AS TOTAL
FROM customer
GROUP BY Payment_Method
ORDER BY COUNT(Payment_Method) DESC;


-- TOP 10 CUSTOMER ACCORDING TO HIGH REVENUE
SELECT 
TOP 10
CustomerID,
Revenue
FROM customer
ORDER BY Revenue DESC;


-- TOP 10 CUSTOMER ACCORDING TO LOW REVENUE
SELECT 
TOP 10
CustomerID,
Revenue
FROM customer
ORDER BY Revenue;

-- AVG REVENUE
SELECT 
AVG(Revenue) AS AVG_REVENUE
FROM customer

-- WHAT IS THE MAX MIN AVG PROFIT MARGIN
SELECT
MAX(Profit_Margin) AS MAX,
MIN(Profit_Margin) AS MIN,
AVG(Profit_Margin) AS AVG
FROM customer;

